parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic power steering system can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering suddenly quits working while driving
the steering wheel shakes or jerks
the vehicle pulls to one side
the ESC (Electronic Stability Control) light comes on
the traction control light comes on
the power steering warning light comes on
the steering wheel locks up
and the vehicle becomes difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents or injuries, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: The brake lights fail to illuminate when the brake pedal is pressed
or they illuminate randomly without the brake pedal being pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering light comes on
the ESC light comes on
the traction control light comes on
the engine reduced power light comes on
and the vehicle goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power door locks can cause inconvenience and safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The power door locks fail to unlock or lock
or they unlock or lock randomly while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause accidents or injuries, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: The headlights fail to illuminate
or they illuminate intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle fails to shift into gear
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission warning light illuminates
the vehicle makes a grinding or whining noise
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ESC warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses traction
the vehicle skids or slides
the vehicle has difficulty steering
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle has a heavy or stiff steering wheel
the vehicle makes a grinding or whining noise.
